Tired of their servitude to man, a group of farm animals revolt and establish their own society, only to be betrayed into worse servitude by their leaders, the pigs, whose slogan becomes: &quot;All animals are equal, but some animals are more equal than others.&quot; This 1945 satire addresses the socialist/ communist philosophy of Stalin in the Soviet Union.
